On World Freedom Day, President Joe Biden reflects on the fall of the Berlin Wall and the triumph of freedom over tyranny. He emphasizes the importance of democracy and the need to defend it against the forces of autocracy. He pledges the United States' commitment to promoting a free, open, secure, and prosperous world. Biden highlights the ongoing struggles for democracy in Ukraine, Iran, Burma, and Cuba, and expresses solidarity with those fighting for their rights. He proclaims November 9, 2022, as World Freedom Day and calls upon the American people to remember the hope represented by the fall of the Berlin Wall and recommit to freedom and democracy.